I recently had the pleasure of visiting The Holy Grind Coffee Shop in the Concord SW area, and I must say it was an exceptional experience. From the moment I walked through the door, I was greeted with a warm and inviting atmosphere that immediately made me feel right at home.

The Holy Grind Coffee Shop boasts a charming interior with cozy seating arrangements, perfect for both catching up with friends or finding a quiet corner to relax and enjoy a good book. The ambiance is complemented by soft lighting and soothing background music, creating a serene environment perfect for a coffee break.

Speaking of coffee, The Holy Grind truly excels in this department. Their selection of coffee and espresso-based beverages is extensive, and the quality is top-notch. I had the pleasure of trying their signature blend, and I was blown away by its rich and robust flavor. The baristas are not only skilled in their craft but also genuinely passionate about creating the perfect cup of coffee. It's evident that they take pride in their work, and it shines through in every sip.

In addition to their exceptional coffee, The Holy Grind offers a variety of delectable pastries and light bites. I indulged in a flaky croissant paired with my coffee, and it was the perfect accompaniment. The menu caters to different tastes and dietary preferences, ensuring there's something for everyone.

What truly sets The Holy Grind Coffee Shop apart is the exceptional service provided by their friendly and attentive staff. From the moment I placed my order to the moment I left, I felt well taken care of. The staff is knowledgeable, accommodating, and always ready with a smile. Their genuine passion for customer satisfaction is evident, and it made my visit all the more enjoyable.

Overall, I highly recommend The Holy Grind Coffee Shop to anyone in the Concord SW area looking for a delightful coffee experience. Whether you're a coffee enthusiast or simply seeking a cozy spot to unwind, this charming establishment will exceed your expectations. I can't wait to visit again and try more of their tantalizing offerings.positive review for The Holy Grind Coffee Shop. In Concord SW area. Highly recommended. reviews_data.review_text:
Food is not bad at all. Quite above the average for what I have seen this region. Kudos for that.
But as a Christian, I find it distasteful that the store tries way too hard to show every living soul that they are Christians. A true Christian should be concerned about one's intimate relationships with their God instead of using it as a marketing ploy, such as that one time I had to walk out 5 seconds after I walked in because this woman guitarist was singing about how "Jesus saved her soul" in the cafe.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
We appreciate your input, but we couldn't disagree more. We are trying to shine the light and love of Jesus Christ in a world that is so broken, dark and hurting and you would prefer us to be more quiet about that? We think that goes against everything Jesus stands for. 

We are not a Christian "based" coffee shop, we ARE a Christian coffee shop. If someone singing about their encounter with Jesus offends you, that's OK. That's your preference, but not something you can force on others. We stand by our openess and unashamed desire to spread the love of Jesus to a lost and dying world. It's not a ploy or anything of the like. 

We serve great coffee and good food (as you stated) but we are a ministry first and foremost.

reviews_data.review_text:
Two disappointing visits within a couple of weeks. Yesterday I stopped in with my Mom to treat her to a coffee and treat on her birthday. The young lady took our order fairly quickly, but it wasn't apparent immediately that there were at least 4-5 orders ahead of us. After waiting 20 minutes to receive our complete order (2 drinks & 2 scones), I took a bite of what was the worst scone I have ever had in my life. It was dry and stale and should not have been sold to me. My breve was mediocre at best.
Another notable mention is the fact that the Manager or Owner was in the shop meeting with some other gentlemen. It was quite clear that this young lady was overwhelmed and VERY slow and he did not offer to help her fulfill the orders to ensure everyone was served in a reasonable amount of time.
20 minutes is too long to wait for good coffee and food let alone poor-quality ones. There are many other great coffee shops in the area, so I won't be returning here.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Tina, thank you for your honest review, even though it does sting a bit. We are thankful for our patrons and those who choose to support us because of what we stand for and because we are small business.

If you ever give us another try, it's all on us. Please understand we are not okay with the service you received.  

We do get some of our pastries from a local baker, and are usually selling out of everything before they can bring more, so this must've been an abnormal occurrence. They're always delicious when fresh. 

Lastly, because others will be reading this I want future customers to be aware, that our manager was in a very important meeting at the time of your encounter. The baristas are aware that they may get a rush of people and will be required to make the drinks alone because a manager may not always be available. To be noted, though, our managers DO NOT leave our baristas high and dry. Once the meeting was completed he went back to help out. 

Rushes happen and waiting for coffee is a normal occurrence at any establishment, but waiting for mediocre coffee is definitely not a win for anyone. This we are sorry for and would love to offer you a free one in its place. 

If you're ever again in the area and need a quick pick me up, please stop in and we will make it right.

reviews_data.review_text: Me and my family went to the china grove location on a Monday afternoon. Looking for a nice quiet spot to enjoy some family time together and a good iced latte. We have frequently stopped by here in the past but stopped as the service was never friendly and yesterday we thought after a year we would try it again. Sadly it hasn’t changed. When we got there the man at the register was very kind and so was the young girl making our drinks. But out of no where another woman steps behind the counter (I assume a manger to help with training) and is just beyond rude and belittling to the employee that took our order that was helping the barista make drinks. So much so that it made me very uncomfortable to even watch.She was so rude and disrespectful I couldn’t believe that anyone would let an employee talk like that to anyone especially with a customer standing right there.I was a manger at a coffee shop for over 3 years and never would I have allowed a situation like that to happen. Totally unprofessional. We spent over $20 for this experience and yes the coffee was great but this whole encounter made me feel so uncomfortable and regretted ever coming back to give this place another chance. We didn’t even stay to drink our coffee and left promptly . You can have a cute and relaxing decorated atmosphere for a coffee shop but if your employees aren’t friendly and kind then what’s the point? It doesn’t make it that people will want to stay or even come back if the customer service is terrible. I’m sorry but I can go to Starbucks or French express for a better experience where employees are friendly and kind. Will definitely not be coming back after that experience. Please do better with your customer service.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Lydia!

Terribly sorry this was your experience. Remember that reviews don't just affect the person you're reviewing...it affects the whole company and the people who really are working at their best to make your experience a memorable one. 

Whomever it was that offended you in such a way is most likely no longer employed with us. We have recently gone through many changes and God has shown us areas of improvement and we have acted on it. 

A 1 star review, especially since your coffee was tasty seems a little harsh to us, but I hope you can give us another chance to show you who we really are. If you visit us again, ask for a manager and make sure your coffee is made to your liking and take a few moments to sit and relax. It's one of the best things about a local coffee shop. 🙂

We would love for you to consider that maybe this was a new barista who was still nervous to share their opinion for fear of being wrong, or maybe they didn't hear you. Either way, we hire our baristas to have a heart for people and occasionally they have an off day. We still stand behind them 🤎
Also, the milks that aren't lactose typically look the exact same in the containers. So, if you did see a container that looked like it was almond, but was most likely oat. Our baristas know not to replace milk without consent. 
To address your pastry issue, we use to have an on-site baker who's business we supported whole heartedly, but she has since moved on and we get our pastries from the most consistent place we can find locally that's within a customer's budget nowadays: Sam's Club.
